Cell.Text: G|Jarl Balgruuf is waiting.

S|You're the one that got out of Helgen, aren't you? I could use anyone who's tangled with a dragon before. | Where do you think you'll be the most help - scouting ahead or supporting the rest of my men?
Well? You going to scout ahead or travel with me?
[S] G|<<Shared>> Follow me. We're assembling near the main gate.
[S] G|Good enough. We'll meet up near the watchtower. Don't take any chances until we get there.
<<Shared>> I can't believe it! You're... Dragonborn...
G|<<Shared>> I can't believe it! You're... Dragonborn...
G|I'm proud to be your battle-brother, Dragonborn. Whiterun doesn't need to fear with you on our side.
G|You sure did for that dragon. Dragonborn or not, that's good enough for me.
G|I can't believe we actually killed a dragon!
G|Dragonborn... it's an honor.
G|You saved Whiterun today. We won't forget.
G|Is it really dead?
G|Come on, I want a better look at that thing.
G|We taught that dragon not to mess with Whiterun, didn't we?
G|I'm glad you're on our side.
[S] G|Get under cover! The dragon - it's still around somewhere!
G|I'm glad you're coming with us. They say Talos favors you.
G|That dragon should've stuck with killing Imperials. Now he's going to learn how real Nords fight.
G|My cousin's stationed out at the watchtower. I hope he's all right.
G|I doubt any of us are coming back from this mission.
G|With Irileth, you either come back covered with glory or not at all.
G|You really think we can kill a dragon?
G|I'm looking forward to testing myself against this dragon.
G|I hear you faced a dragon at Helgen and lived to tell about it. That ain't nothing.
G|We'd better keep moving. Who knows what that dragon is doing.
G|I hope the tower holds out until we get there.
G|This doesn't look good.
G|Shor's bones, did it kill them all...?
G|We'd better find out what's happened.
G|We'd better keep moving.
G|Good luck. I hope you get there in time.
G|Hold on. I want to hear what Irileth's saying.
That may be true, but I ordered Irileth to bring back proof. You'd best report back to her at once.
G|We'd better go make sure that bastard is really dead. Collect us a trophy or something to bring back to Ulfric.
G|Scatter and get behind cover! We need to hurt it, somehow! If you've got a bow or spells, now would be a good time to use them!

GS|That was the hairiest fight I've ever been in, and I've been in more than a few. | I don't know about this Dragonborn business, but I'm sure glad you're with us. | You better get back to Whiterun right away. Jarl Balgruuf will want to know what happened here.
G|I'm taking command here for the moment. You head back to Whiterun and let the Jarl know what happened.
G|Be careful. We need to find out what happened here.
[S] G|If you really are Dragonborn, then Skyrim needs you. Go to High Hrothgar and talk to the Greybeards.
G|<<Shared>> We were just talking about you. My brother needs a word with you.
You've done a great service for me and my city, Dragonborn.
So what happened at the watchtower? Was the dragon there?
G|Help Irileth kill this dragon before it can attack Whiterun. There's no time to lose.

There's no time to stand on ceremony, my friend. I need your help again. | I want you to go with Irileth and help her fight this dragon. | You survived Helgen, so you have more experience with dragons than anyone else here.
G|Not now.
I knew I could count on Irileth. But there must be more to it than that.

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroA1: The watchtower was destroyed, but we killed the dragon.

Cell.Text: Dragonborn? What do you know about the Dragonborn?

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroA2: Turns out I may be something called "Dragonborn".

Cell.Text: There's no question about that. It was a mighty deed. You've earned a place of honor among the heroes of Whiterun. | But there must be more to it than that. Did something... strange... happen when the dragon died?

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroA3: I killed the dragon. I think I deserve a reward.

Cell.Text: [S] So it's true. The Greybeards really were summoning you.

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroB1: When the dragon died, I absorbed some kind of power from it.

Cell.Text: [S] Not just the men. The Greybeards seem to think the same thing.

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroB2: That's just what the men called me.

Cell.Text: Masters of the Way of the Voice. They live in seclusion high on the slopes of the Throat of the World.

[S] The Dragonborn is said to be uniquely gifted in the Voice - the ability to focus your vital essence into a thu'um, or Shout. | The Greybeards are masters of the Way of the Voice. If you really are Dragonborn, they can teach you how to use your gift.

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroC2: What do these Greybeards want with me?

Cell.Text: [S] Well, in the old tales, the Dragonborn heroes would use the power of their Voice to defeat the enemies of Skyrim. | In the very oldest tales, back from when there still were dragons in Skryim, the Dragonborn would slay dragons and steal their power. | That's what you did, isn't it? Absorbed that dragon's power?
G|Well, you can Shout now. You couldn't before, right? That can only mean one thing. You must be Dragonborn.
G|There's one way to find out. Try to Shout... that would prove it. Only the Dragonborn can Shout without training, the way the dragons do.

Node.Caption: MQ104ADragonbornB1: I don't know what happened to me.

Cell.Text: G|Yes. I think I am. You can Shout now. That can only mean one thing. You must be Dragonborn.
G|There's one way to find out. Try to Shout... Only the Dragonborn can Shout without training, the way the dragons do.

Node.Caption: MQ104ADragonbornB2: I think you may be right.

Cell.Text: G|I want to find out about this dragon.

[S] The Dragonborn is said to be uniquely gifted in the Voice - the ability to focus your vital essence into a thu'um, or Shout. | If you really are Dragonborn, they can teach you how to use your gift.

Node.Caption: MQ104BalgruufOutroD1: What do these Greybeards want with me?

Cell.Text: [S] G|But I haven't forgotten the service you did for me in retrieving the dragonstone for Farengar. | As a token of my esteem, I have instructed Avenicci that you are now permitted to purchase property in the city. | And please accept this gift from my personal armory.

[S] G|By my right as Jarl, I name you Thane of Whiterun. It's the greatest honor that's within my power to grant. | I assign you Lydia as a personal Housecarl, and this weapon from my armory to serve as your badge of office. | I'll also notify my guards of your new title. Wouldn't want them to think you're part of the common rabble, now. | We are honored to have you as Thane of our city, Dragonborn.
